<h2>Rapid Descriptions</h2>
<div><div id='zzqdo1q7s3v9kh0RiverRapidView65' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid100361">Bridge Abutments</a></b> (Class III, Mile 0.5)<br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>Bridge Abutments</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqdo1q7s3v9kh0PhotoDetailView133' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/11373/size/big/">
<img class='riverdetail' src="/photos/archive/medium/11373.jpg">
</a>
<i>Bridge Abutments</i></div><div>Photo taken 07/10/05 @ ~2.8ft</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
<p>The bridge abutments can be safely navigated down the center of the river, or for a more challenging line, on river right. These abutments were the site of a fatality when a boater became pinned there. Exercise caution.</p><br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqdo1q7s3v9kh0RiverRapidView66' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid100360">Main Hole</a></b> (Class III, Mile 0.7)<br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>Bob Taylor at T'ville</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqdo1q7s3v9kh0PhotoDetailView137' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/1038/size/big/">
<img class='riverdetail' src="/photos/archive/medium/1038.jpg">
</a>
<i>Bob Taylor at T'ville</i></div><div>Photo of Tariffville by Michael Phelan @ 3</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
<p>This hole, and several surrounding it, are the most popular features on this section of the river. The majority of boaters park at the end of Tunxis Ave and walk or paddle down to this location and surf. You can either walk back up to the parking lot from this point if you like.</p><br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqdo1q7s3v9kh0RiverRapidView67' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid100362">Former Location of Spoonville Dam</a></b> (Class III+, Mile 1.0)<br>
<p>
This formerly broken dam was removed in 2012. No notable rapids exist in its former location.</p>
<br>
